581
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:28,680
What I want to get rid of

582
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:30,000
is only the physical pain.

583
00:36:30,840 --> 00:36:31,880
I feel that

584
00:36:31,880 --> 00:36:33,880
after experiencing the darkest moments,

585
00:36:33,880 --> 00:36:35,280
they have come, and they were painful,

586
00:36:35,280 --> 00:36:36,160
I then realized

587
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:37,320
that every moment after that

588
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:38,760
is happy and bright.

589
00:36:38,760 --> 00:36:39,800
I will have something to look forward to.

590
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:42,160
There will be a source of spiritual support.

591
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:43,960
But when it comes to physical pain,

592
00:36:43,960 --> 00:36:45,320
the less, the better.

593
00:36:45,320 --> 00:36:47,280
It really hurts, it really does.

594
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:51,320
Actually, what I want to erase even more

595
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:53,280
are the especially happy memories from this time.

596
00:36:54,120 --> 00:36:54,920
Because after experiencing

597
00:36:54,920 --> 00:36:56,040
so many wonderful things,

598
00:36:56,040 --> 00:36:57,360
when you return to your own life,

599
00:36:57,360 --> 00:36:59,000
you're especially afraid you'll never experience them again.

600
00:36:59,000 --> 00:37:00,360
The bar is set so high.

601
00:37:00,360 --> 00:37:01,440
The standard is right here.

602
00:37:01,440 --> 00:37:05,880
So this happiness feels too heavy.

603
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:06,760
It's just too much.

604
00:37:06,760 --> 00:37:08,120
Even though sometimes I feel

605
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:08,960
that I've already returned to my normal life,

606
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:09,880
for some time now,

607
00:37:09,880 --> 00:37:10,680
it seems like those days

608
00:37:10,680 --> 00:37:11,960
are just a part of my memories.

609
00:37:11,960 --> 00:37:12,880
But when you look back at it again,

610
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:13,720
at this experience,

611
00:37:14,600 --> 00:37:17,200
You would still find it so moving.

612
00:37:17,200 --> 00:37:19,120
I think this question actually

613
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:21,160
can be looked at from two perspectives.

614
00:37:21,680 --> 00:37:23,600
If you only keep the good memories

615
00:37:23,880 --> 00:37:24,440
and none of the bad ones,

616
00:37:24,440 --> 00:37:25,960
it's actually a false proposition.

617
00:37:26,320 --> 00:37:26,760
So,

618
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:28,640
to make the good ones even better,

619
00:37:28,640 --> 00:37:31,560
there must be some bad ones as well.

620
00:37:32,600 --> 00:37:33,840
Also, I think

621
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:34,760
as I get older,

622
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:37,200
I value more and more

623
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:39,400
the experience and process over the outcome.

624
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:41,400
When you value the experience

625
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:42,320
more than the result,

626
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:46,200
you might not care as much

627
00:37:46,200 --> 00:37:47,640
about those unpleasant memories.

628
00:37:47,640 --> 00:37:48,560
Right.

629
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:50,040
Process-oriented.

630
00:37:50,040 --> 00:37:50,360
Yes.

631
00:37:50,360 --> 00:37:51,600
If you are process-oriented,

632
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:54,680
you might tend to keep everything,

633
00:37:54,680 --> 00:37:56,200
because it's all part of your experience.

634
00:37:56,200 --> 00:37:57,360
It's all part of who you are.

635
00:37:58,800 --> 00:38:00,040
But I actually really disagree

636
00:38:00,040 --> 00:38:01,000
with Lao Luo on that point.

637
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:03,640
You said that because everyone is already doing well,

638
00:38:03,640 --> 00:38:05,720
and you're afraid that you might never reach

639
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:06,320
this level again in the future,

640
00:38:06,320 --> 00:38:08,120
so you might as well not have it at all.

641
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:10,680
So if you know

642
00:38:10,680 --> 00:38:11,520
there might not be a result,

643
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:12,920
would you still want to start it?

644
00:38:13,280 --> 00:38:14,880
I would definitely choose to start it.

645
00:38:14,880 --> 00:38:16,480
Its meaning is that

646
00:38:17,120 --> 00:38:19,680
even if there will definitely be a separation,

647
00:38:19,680 --> 00:38:21,240
the part of me that changed

648
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:23,160
because of you

649
00:38:23,160 --> 00:38:25,360
will stay with me forever in your place.

650
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:26,240
That's enough.

651
00:38:26,240 --> 00:38:26,800
Yes.

652
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:27,400
We all have

653
00:38:27,400 --> 00:38:29,080
a part of each of you in us.

654
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:30,000
Right.

655
00:38:30,480 --> 00:38:32,280
And I think we're all in our thirties now,

656
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:34,480
so we do have some ability to keep this going.

657
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:35,320
That's what I personally think.

658
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:36,280
Yes.

659
00:38:36,280 --> 00:38:37,040
We definitely will.

660
00:38:37,040 --> 00:38:38,480
Are you saying this for Wo Wo to hear?

661
00:38:38,880 --> 00:38:39,800
You said it for Wo Wo.

662
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:41,320
It's nothing.

663
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:43,160
You should be able to come, right?

664
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:49,520
And just now, watching that,

665
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:51,360
everyone was leaving with their suitcases.

666
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:53,320
As we left the cabin one by one,

667
00:38:53,640 --> 00:38:55,760
what were everyone's feelings at that moment?

668
00:38:56,120 --> 00:38:57,440
I once read a saying,

669
00:38:57,440 --> 00:38:59,000
"If you come, I will surely greet you.

670
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:00,600
If you leave, I don't need to see you off."

671
00:39:01,680 --> 00:39:02,600
So in this situation, I feel that

672
00:39:02,600 --> 00:39:04,040
when each person was leaving,

673
00:39:04,040 --> 00:39:05,960
everyone just said goodbye.

674
00:39:05,960 --> 00:39:08,120
But we wouldn't say it

675
00:39:08,120 --> 00:39:08,960
in an overly dramatic way.

676
00:39:08,960 --> 00:39:10,120
Because I think, deep down,

677
00:39:10,120 --> 00:39:10,560
we all believe

678
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:11,960
that we will meet again.

679
00:39:12,680 --> 00:39:14,520
Anyway, Wanwan and Yanyan

680
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:16,160
were here for the shortest time.

681
00:39:16,160 --> 00:39:16,480
Yes.

682
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:17,120
That's right.

683
00:39:17,120 --> 00:39:18,360
But actually, the feelings

684
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:19,800
were still very deep.

685
00:39:20,880 --> 00:39:22,360
Even though the time spent was short,

686
00:39:23,040 --> 00:39:24,840
the experience was very meaningful.

687
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:27,000
We felt a lot.

688
00:39:27,640 --> 00:39:28,720
Just like Lao Luo said,

689
00:39:29,040 --> 00:39:30,920
I believe we will meet again.

690
00:39:30,920 --> 00:39:32,160
I believe when we meet again,

691
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:34,040
it will be just like before,

692
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:36,280
happily and comfortably together.

693
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:38,280
So for me,

694
00:39:38,280 --> 00:39:39,840
it's just that this chapter has ended,

695
00:39:39,840 --> 00:39:41,760
not our story as a whole.

696
00:39:45,120 --> 00:39:47,880
I remember it very clearly,

697
00:39:47,880 --> 00:39:49,920
you were the one who brought me into this little house.

698
00:39:49,920 --> 00:39:51,480
Do you remember that moment?

699
00:39:52,640 --> 00:39:53,640
Yes, I do.

700
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:56,040
And when it was time to leave, you saw me off.

701
00:39:56,040 --> 00:39:58,320
You said goodbye to me.

702
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:00,640
At that moment, I felt like

703
00:40:00,640 --> 00:40:02,640
just a moment ago, you had brought me into

704
00:40:03,040 --> 00:40:03,760
this house.

705
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:05,200
You were introducing it to me,

706
00:40:05,200 --> 00:40:05,960
saying this place is

707
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:07,680
a very magical little house.

708
00:40:07,680 --> 00:40:09,280
And then, it was all over in an instant.

709
00:40:14,320 --> 00:40:15,120
But actually, I think

710
00:40:15,120 --> 00:40:16,880
it's normal for everyone to feel sad when they see farewells.

711
00:40:16,880 --> 00:40:17,960
That's perfectly normal.

712
00:40:17,960 --> 00:40:18,880
But there's a saying that I really like.

713
00:40:18,880 --> 00:40:20,520
It says that farewells are

714
00:40:20,520 --> 00:40:21,920
the second most romantic thing in the world.

715
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:23,600
Because with farewells, there will be reunions.

716
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:24,200
And reunions

717
00:40:24,200 --> 00:40:25,400
are the most romantic thing.

718
00:40:29,240 --> 00:40:30,120
So in just a short

719
00:40:30,120 --> 00:40:31,440
period of time,

720
00:40:31,440 --> 00:40:35,120
we've experienced meeting, parting, and reuniting.

721
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:36,760
We've truly experienced

722
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:37,920
the most romantic things in the world.

723
00:40:38,760 --> 00:40:39,400
Yes.

724
00:40:39,400 --> 00:40:40,720
And now, until

725
00:40:40,720 --> 00:40:42,040
the end of the fourth season of "Half Mature Lovers,"

726
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:43,320
there's only one episode left.

727
00:40:43,320 --> 00:40:45,120
I believe everyone will feel reluctant to say goodbye.

728
00:40:45,440 --> 00:40:47,200
So I hope everyone will keep following

729
00:40:47,200 --> 00:40:48,400
the fourth season of "Half Mature Lovers."

730
00:40:48,400 --> 00:40:50,040
Today's

731
00:40:50,040 --> 00:40:51,440
watch-along of episode nine

732
00:40:51,440 --> 00:40:52,760
ends here.

733
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:54,840
Be sure to stay tuned to

734
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:55,400
Tencent Video.

735
00:40:55,400 --> 00:40:56,600
See you next time.

736
